  "texts": [
    "Table 3.1 shows the breakdown of the labeled dataset.",
    "One sentence can be tagged with multiple labels because of the independence of prices, demand, and supply.",
    "Zero Shot LearningThis study employs a zero-shot learning approach to evaluate the performance of two prominent language models, FinBERT and RoBERTa-Large, as seen in table 3.2, in establishing a baseline for the sentiment analysis of oil market articles.",
    "The objective is to assess the inherent capacity of these models to generalize to unseen data and tasks, thereby providing a benchmark for future research in this area.This study further extends the zero-shot learning paradigm to LLMs.",
    "To obtain economically relevant insights, we employ engineered prompts designed in consultation with economists."
  ]
